Hindawi is a word of [[Urdu]] / [[Arabic]] origin that literally means Indian. It is a commonly used [[Arabic]] [[family name]]. The word is supposed to be the root of the word [[Hindi]], which is the [[national language]] of [[India]].

[[Amir Khusro]] called the language of his creative writing Hindawi.

